# KE3P · KEEPER PLATFORM
## Presents — The Missing Layer Between Object and Treatment
*Specification Document · May 2026 · Phase 2*

For: Claude · Cursor · Kip · Chuck

---

## 1. The Decision That Produced This Document

Frames were retired as a platform concept. The builder model was wrong — a domain owner composing a page from component catalogs, publishing a designed surface. That was the wrong assumption about what the guest experiences.

But the presentation problem Frames were trying to solve is real. It did not retire with them.

When a guest arrives at a domain, something receives them. When a Journey surfaces, it has a form. When a Moment plays, it has a shape. These forms needed a name.

> *Presents are that name.*

This document defines Presents — what they are, how they sit in the architecture, how they are rendered, and what must be built before any Cursor prompt about Presents or KeeperPresence is written.

---

## 2. What a Present Is

A Present is the named form a kept object takes when it surfaces to an audience.

Presents are universal. A Cover is a Cover — a Domain can inhabit it, a Journey can inhabit it, a Keeper can inhabit it. The object brings its content. The Present is the form. Treatment governs how that form feels.

> *The platform's render stack is now three layers, each doing one job:*
>
> **Object → Present → Treatment**

This is not a page-builder model. A domain owner does not compose a Present from parts. A Present is intrinsic to the object — the object knows how to inhabit a Cover. Rendr determines which Present is appropriate for a given object in a given context. The owner approves. The platform renders.

### What a Present Is Not

A Present is not a Frame. Frames were authored by composing component catalogs. Presents are configuration — named forms that objects inhabit.

A Present is not a prop. Props are individual field-level display decisions. A Present is the whole form — the named presentation mode.

A Present is not a Treatment. Treatment governs how the Present feels — its spatial ratios, motion behavior, density, presence, atmosphere. The Present governs what the surface is. These are two different layers and must not be collapsed.

---

## 3. The Filmstrip Model

Keeper Presents like a media filmstrip. A presentation has a structure that is independent of what fills it. The content changes. The Present is the form it takes.

| Present | What It Is | Who Can Inhabit It |
|---|---|---|
| **Cover** | The arrival surface. The first thing seen. What receives a guest. | Domain, Journey, Keeper, Moment |
| **Slide** | A structured narrative beat. Content forward, narrative context present. | Journey, Moment, Keeper |
| **Media** | A filmstrip moment. The content is experiential — video, photo, audio. Not read. Felt. | Moment, Domain |
| **Journey** | The story arc surface. The narrative rendered for an audience. Earns its own name because Journey drives the domain. | Journey |
| **Moment** | A single story beat at full depth. Earns its own name because a Moment at full depth is distinct from a Moment in a slide. | Moment |

> This catalog is open. These five are the names confirmed with confidence. Others will emerge from content — not from architecture. Do not invent names before content demands them.

