## 5. Rendr's Expanded Role

Rendr's role expands with this document. Rendr does not just configure Treatment. Rendr reasons about which Present is appropriate for a given object in a given context — and then configures the Treatment that governs how that Present feels.

Rendr also authors Theatre.js sequences — the definitions of what a Cover actually does, what a Journey surface actually unfolds. These are stored with the Present definition and approved by the owner before anything renders.

| Rendr Reasons From | What It Supplies |
|---|---|
| Object type | What kind of object is inhabiting this Present |
| Present name | What form the object is taking |
| Domain identity | Purpose, tone, and audience of the domain |
| Content character | Memorial archive, business pitch, family story, venue |
| Treatment tier | Standard, Cinematic, or Immersive — the motion library constraint |
| Audience | Who is receiving this, in what context, with what expectations |

> *Rendr proposes. The owner approves. Nothing renders without confirmation.*

