## 6. What Must Happen Before Any Cursor Prompt

This decision — that KeeperPresence is a Theatre.js listener, not a static component tree — must be made before any build prompt about Presents or KeeperPresence is written. Retrofitting Theatre.js into a static component architecture is the wrong order.

| Step | What |
|---|---|
| 1 | Confirm Theatre.js SSR compatibility with Vercel/Next.js before installation. This is a prerequisite, not an assumption. |
| 2 | Name performance targets — frame rate, bundle budget, render constraints — before Theatre.js is installed. |
| 3 | Write the Present definition schema — the JSON structure that includes present name, sequence reference, and subject. |
| 4 | Update KeeperPresence signature — add `present` field alongside `context` and `treatment`. |
| 5 | Build KeeperPresence as a Theatre.js listener with placeholder sequences for the five named Presents. |
| 6 | Rendr authors real sequences when Rendr is built. Placeholder sequences are the scaffold, not the destination. |

