## 9. Canonical Terms

Every term below is locked for Presents. Do not substitute synonyms.

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Present | The named form a kept object takes when it surfaces to an audience. Universal — any object can inhabit any Present. |
| PresentName | The string type for a Present identifier. Open — not a closed enum. `'cover'` \| `'slide'` \| `'media'` \| `'journey'` \| `'moment'` \| `string`. |
| Cover | The arrival surface. The first thing a guest sees. Any object can inhabit it. |
| Slide | A structured narrative beat. Content forward, narrative context present. |
| Media | A filmstrip moment. The content is experiential — video, photo, audio. Not read. Felt. |
| Journey (Present) | The story arc surface. The narrative rendered for an audience. Distinct from Journey as an object type. |
| Moment (Present) | A single story beat at full depth. Distinct from Moment as an object type. |
| Present sequence | The Theatre.js sequence definition that governs how a Present unfolds. Authored by Rendr. Approved by owner. |
| KeeperPresence | The universal render component. Receives object, present, context, and treatment. Responds to Theatre.js values. Does not branch on present name. |

